7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to consumer protection; to amend Sections
10 8-42-1, 8-42-2, and 8-42-3, Section 34-27-2, as last amended
11 by 2025-380, 2025 Regular Session, Sections 34-27-30 and
12 34-27-36, as last amended by 2025-308, 2025 Regular Session,
13 Code of Alabama 1975; to define "equitable interest" and "real
14 estate wholesaling,"; to require certain disclosures in
15 wholesaling transactions; to require a real estate wholesaler
16 to be licensed with the Alabama Real Estate Commission; to
17 provide that the Alabama Securities Commission has concurrent
18 jurisdiction with the Alabama Real Estate Commission to
19 regulate real estate wholesaling; to provide that failure to
20 provide the required disclosures may subject the wholesaler to
21 fines and penalties; to authorize the Alabama Real Estate
22 Commission to refer real estate wholesaling matters to the
23 Alabama Securities Commission for investigation and
24 enforcement; Sections 8-42-1.1, 8-42-1.2, 8-42-1.3, and 8-42-4
25 are added to the Code of Alabama 1975; to authorize the
26 Alabama Securities Commission to enforce violations of
27 investment-oriented real property solicitation disclosure
28 requirements; to provide that the Alabama Securities
Page 1

requirements; to provide that the Alabama Securities
HB586 Engrossed
29 Commission has concurrent jurisdiction with the Alabama Real
30 Estate Commission to regulate real estate wholesaling; to
31 provide fines and penalties for wholesaling and unsolicited
32 offer violations; to provide for rescission of unsolicited
33 real estate contracts in certain circumstances; to authorize
34 the Alabama Securities Commission to establish standard
35 disclosure language for investment-oriented solicitations; and
36 to also make nonsubstantive, technical revisions to update the
37 existing code language to current style.
