161 (a) For purposes of this section the following terms
162 have the following meanings:
163 (1) RECORDING. Presenting a document to a county judge
164 of probate for official placement in the public land records.
165 (2) RESIDENTIAL REAL ESTATE. Real property located in
166 this state which is used primarily for a dwelling and contains
167 one to four dwelling units.
168 (3) SERVICE AGREEMENT. A contract under which a person
